Kiwi.Plugins.name: Kiwi.Plugins
Kiwi.Plugins.description:
ParticlePack3 contains factory methods to create particles for your KiwiJS
game. Use the `create` methods to generate particles or groups of particles.

For a walkthrough on setting up the particle pack plugin check the README.

Kiwi.Plugins.ParticlePack3.name: Kiwi.Plugins.ParticlePack3
Kiwi.Plugins.ParticlePack3.description:
ParticlePack3 contains factory methods to create particles for your KiwiJS
game. Use the `create` methods to generate particles or groups of particles.

For a walkthrough on setting up the particle pack plugin check the README.

classitems.description: The version of this plugin in semver (semantic versioning) format
classitems.name: version

classitems.description:
The minimum version of Kiwi.js required to run this plugin in semver
(semantic versioning) format
classitems.name: minimumKiwiVersion

classitems.description: Other plugins required for this plugin to run.
classitems.name: pluginDependencies

classitems.description:
Create and return an effect. This is invoked by the individual effects
and should not be used by developers.
classitems.name: _create

return.description: Particle effect or group of particle effects

classitems.description: Run `scheduleStop` on all members of an effect group.
classitems.name: scheduleStop

params.name: milliseconds
params.description: Delay time in milliseconds before stopping

classitems.description: Run `startEmitting` on all members of an effect group.
classitems.name: startEmitting

params.name: loop
params.description:
Set to true for continuous looping.
	Overrides and updates the config loop setting.

params.name: removeOnComplete
params.description:
If not looping, then
	the gameobject will destroy itself after one full emission cycle.

params.name: numParts
params.description:
Number of particles to generate,
	set on the config object - if not provided
	the current config value will be used

classitems.description: Run `stopEmitting` on all members of an effect group.
classitems.name: stopEmitting

params.name: immediate
params.description:
Stops the emitter
	and removes any existing particles.

params.name: remove
params.description:
If true the gameobject will mark itself
	for removal either immediately, or after a completed cycle.
